Description:
CHP wishes to commission a supplier to provide the following services and/or works to all domestic lifting equipment (stair lifts, through floor lifts, wheelchair/platform lifts and ceiling/bath hoists) to properties in the area covered by CHP (Essex):

• Regular inspection, servicing, maintenance and repair;
• Provision of a prompt 24-hour breakdown/call out service;
• Equipment removal.

The aim of the pilot programme is to:
• amplify the voice of ONS G7/G6 EM colleagues;
• broaden networks and opportunities beyond EM
communities and ONS;
• connect the experiences and thinking of our diverse
communities, line managers and senior leaders, to learn and grow together in this space;
• further explore and address cultural and organisational
issues relating to retention of EM colleagues;
• strengthen a community of support.

The object of the framework is to supply several different aerial works services, these may include but are not limited to;
1.1.	Airlifting of underslung loads;
1.2.	Movement of personnel;
1.3.	Movement of materials 
1.4.	Aerial filming.
